Description: Fragment of oval handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora to moderate turn. Clay fine light red-brown; cream slip. Rectangular stamp with 'Helios Symbol' as symbol and Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Trimmed. Name Armosilas. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0081.37.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0684)
